provenance_domain.name: Cancer gene expression across cell types (scRNA-seq pilot)

pipeline_steps.description: Instructions in Instructions_for_scRNA_Data.txt were followed in R to download outputfilename1.csv and outputfilename2.csv
SRA run accessions corresponding with cell groups listed in samples_for_retrieval.csv were identified and isolated in counts_input.csv[intermediate]
Cell groups and SRA run accessions in counts_input.csv were identified and listed in map_input.csv[intermediate]
scRNA_Pool&Norm.py was run to generate transformed.csv[intermediate]
Ensemble gene IDs were mapped to SwissProt reviewed UniProtKB accessions
PEM scores were calculated from count values in transformed.csv and expression specificity was determined
Expression level was determined from PEM score
All calculated values are reported in the final output file.

usability_domain: List of human [taxid:9606] genes with expression in cells analyzed from scRNA-seq data - This file contains log2 transformed and pooled gene-level counts from cancer scRNA-Seq data for cell groups whose IDs have been mapped to Cellosaurus. Additionally, the file features the Disease Ontology (DOID) and cancer type associated with each cell group, the number of samples pooled, the PEM score calculated, expression specificity reported from the PEM score, and expression level determined from multiple quantitative expression criteria.

provenance_domain.name: Human cancer (CDO slim) to tissue ontology (Uberon) mapping

pipeline_steps.description: The file CancerDOSlim2.1_local_HMD_5Sep2018.xlsx (not in server) was filtered to remove terms "DOID:305 / carcinoma" and "DOID:0070003 / blastoma"

Interim file was then altered such that term "DOID:3963 / thyroid carcinoma" was changed to "DOID:1781 / thryoid cancer" and term "DOID:3119 / gastrointestinal system cancer" was changed to "DOID:9253 / gastrointestinal stromal tumor"
Remaining DOIDs were mapped manually to corresponding UBERON Anatomical Entity ID using the current DO owl file doid.owl (in server)
UBERON Anatomical Entity names were manually retrieved by querying the corresponding UBERON ID at ontobee.org
Resulting information was output in human_doid_slim_uberon_mapping.csv

usability_domain: Human Cancer Disease Ontology Slim IDs (V2.1) directly mapped to UBERON Anatomical Entity IDs - The csv file human_doid_uberon_mapping.csv contains slim-level Disease Ontology IDs (DOIDs) from the Cancer DO Slim project mapped to the corresponding tissue in the UBERON Anatomical Entity Ontology.

provenance_domain.name: Cancer cell-type expression specificity table

pipeline_steps.description: R commands were used with the recount Bioconductor package to retrieve gene-level count matrices and sample information for all runs in target studies
Count matrices were manually filtered for all replicate runs of target cancer cell types
Count matrices were normalized with SCnorm using default parameters
Replicate runs in normalized count matrices were pooled by calculating mean values per cancer cell type
Count matrices were merged into forpemdatafiltered.csv and this input file with transcriptlist.csv was used with the script pemscorescriptfiltered.R to calculate PEM scores
The input file, pemscoreswithtranscriptsfiltered.csv, was used to determine expression type annotations with the script expressiontyping.py

organizer2.py was used with pemscoreswithtranscriptsfiltered.csv and type_sheet_filtered.csv as input files to merge PEM scores, expression type annotations, and cell type information into human_cancer_scRNA_expression.csv
VLOOKUP was used with human_cancer_genes.csv and ensembl_to_gene_symbol.txt to map gene symbols and uniprot accessions to Ensembl gene ids in human_cancer_scRNA_expression.csv

Identifier mapping to ensembl gene ids in human_cancer_scRNA_expression.csv was manually quality checked by searching for five ensembl gene ids with no matching identifiers in  uniprot.org. Additionally, ten uniprot accessions  were checked in uniprot.org for corresponding mapped gene symbols

usability_domain: Master results table of cancer cell-type expression specificity data. The csv file human_cancer_scRNA_expression contains expression specificity scores, expression specificity annotations, and associated disease information for cancer cell types.

provenance_domain.name: Human cancer driver mutations table

pipeline_steps.description: mmc1.xlsx was downloaded from https://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(18)30237-X#sec4.1
Table S4 in mmc1.xlsx was copied to an independent data file and saved as human_cancer_driver_muts.csv
mut_modifier.py script was used to generate three columns describing cancer driver mutations from column “Mutation” in human_cancer_driver_muts.csv
Uniprot accessions were mapped to gene symbols in human_cancer_driver_muts.csv using VLOOKUP with human_cancer_genes.csv
All uniprot accession and gene symbol mapping to ensembl transcript ids was manually checked in human_cancer_genes.csv

usability_domain: Comprehensive cancer driver mutations table. The file human_cancer_driver_muts.csv contains a list of gene symbols and ensembl transcript ids mapped to cancer driver mutations predicted by three structural analysis level computational tools. The csv file human_cancer_driver_muts contains ensembl transcript ids, gene symbols, and computationally determined cancer driver mutations.The csv file human_cancer_driver_muts contains ensembl transcript ids, gene symbols, and computationally determined cancer driver mutations.

provenance_domain.name: Hepatocellular carcinoma serum glycoprotein N-glycan intensity measures

pipeline_steps.description: The XLS file 112019 GTyperSamples APB.xlsx was converted to csv format.
Measured intensity values were normalized across all 50 glycans separately for each individual patient and for each captured serum protein.
An average normalized intensity value was separately calculated for each glycan in each cohort for each protein.
The data format (organization) was reorganized for OncoMX integration.

usability_domain: The glycotyper dataset displays normalized intensity values detected and quantified by Matrix Assisted Laser Desorption Ionization Mass Spectrometry Imaging (MALDI-MSI) for N-glycans of specific serum proteins across Hepatocellular carcinoma and other patient cohorts such as transplant and cirrhosis.

provenance_domain.name: Metadata for differentially gene expression analysis from tumor samples

pipeline_steps.description: The file was downloaded from the NIH GDC portal [https://portal.gdc.cancer.gov/repository].

The cases selected were based on the criteria - files.analysis.workflow_type in [HTSeq - Counts]  and files.data_type in [Gene Expression Quantification] and cases.samples.sample_type in [Primary Tumor] and cases.project.program.name in [TCGA].
With the above mentioned filter criteria, data of a total of 9897 cases with primary tumor was downloaded.
The data format (organization) was reorganized for OncoMX integration.
Resulting information was output in human_cancer_metadata.csv

usability_domain: Clinical data from cancer samples from TCGA datasets that were corresponding to the data used for differential gene expression analysis (Meta data for BioXpress V4.0).
